# Conclusions and Recommendations — Supply Chain Analytics (2024)

Analysis based on 300 simulated purchase orders processed throughout 2024.

**Total Procurement Spend:** R$ 3,466,688

---

## Executive Summary

| Metric                | Result     |
| --------------------- | ---------- |
| Total Purchase Orders | 300        |
| On-Time Delivery Rate | 77.0%      |
| Average Lead Time     | 8.8 days   |
| Delayed Orders        | 69 (23.0%) |

The analysis indicates that supplier performance is the primary operational risk within the procurement process. Nearly one in four purchase orders was delivered late, potentially impacting institutional planning and resource availability.

Additionally, procurement spending is highly concentrated in a small number of categories and products, increasing dependency and supply-chain risk.

---

## 1. Supplier Performance and SLA Compliance

### Suppliers with Highest Delay Rates

| Supplier         | Delay Rate | Average Delay |
| ---------------- | ---------- | ------------- |
| LimpaTudo        | 100.0%     | +9.0 days     |
| EduMaterial      | 34.2%      | +1.3 days     |
| MobiDesk         | 28.6%      | +1.0 day      |
| NetConnect       | 24.1%      | —             |
| CleanPro Higiene | 22.2%      | +0.7 day      |

### Key Insight

LimpaTudo represents the most critical supplier risk in the portfolio. Every purchase order associated with this supplier was delivered after the agreed lead time, with delays averaging nine additional days.

EduMaterial and MobiDesk also exceeded the acceptable delay threshold of 20%, indicating recurring SLA compliance issues.

### Recommendations

* Review supplier performance with LimpaTudo and EduMaterial.
* Introduce contractual penalties for recurring delivery delays.
* Qualify alternative suppliers for cleaning and educational materials.
* Establish monthly SLA monitoring for MobiDesk and NetConnect.

---

## 2. Procurement Spend Concentration

### Spend by Category

| Category              | Spend        | Share |
| --------------------- | ------------ | ----- |
| Technology            | R$ 1,229,660 | 35.5% |
| Audiovisual Equipment | R$ 1,170,050 | 33.8% |
| Furniture             | R$ 894,160   | 25.8% |
| Educational Materials | R$ 86,375    | 2.5%  |
| Office Supplies       | R$ 51,675    | 1.5%  |
| Cleaning Supplies     | R$ 34,768    | 1.0%  |

### Key Insight

Technology, Audiovisual Equipment, and Furniture account for approximately 95% of total procurement spending.

This concentration creates financial exposure and increases dependence on a limited supplier base.

### Recommendations

* Negotiate annual agreements for high-spend categories.
* Maintain at least two approved suppliers per strategic category.
* Consolidate low-value purchases to reduce administrative effort.

