# Priority Action Plan

| Priority | Action                                             | Expected Impact                                                |
| -------- | -------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| High     | Review or replace LimpaTudo                        | Eliminate the highest supplier-related delivery risk           |
| High     | Establish annual agreements for strategic products | Improve cost control across more than 50% of procurement spend |
| Medium   | Monitor EduMaterial and MobiDesk monthly           | Reduce overall delivery delays                                 |
| Medium   | Anticipate Furniture and Audiovisual purchases     | Minimize seasonal delivery risks                               |
| Low      | Consolidate low-value purchases                    | Reduce administrative overhead                                 |

---

## Final Conclusion

The procurement operation demonstrates acceptable overall performance but presents clear opportunities for improvement in supplier management and spend concentration.

The most impactful actions involve improving supplier accountability, diversifying critical suppliers, and strengthening procurement planning for high-value products and peak-demand periods.

By addressing these areas, the organization can improve service levels, reduce operational risk, and increase procurement efficiency without significant process changes.

